### [Psalms Chapter 129](../../../bib/kjv/psa129.htm#001.md)

Psalm 129 recurs now with joy to the sorrows and trials through which
the children of Zion have gone. But Jehovah is righteous, and has cut
asunder the cords of the wicked. The haters of Zion (for Zion is here
always the central thought) are withered, without resource, and without
being desired.

